property includes a mountain that is 233 meters high. Fushimi Inari Shrine is famous for its distinctive red pillars called tori.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 1: JAKARTA – NARITA</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\nAt the appointed time, you will gather at Soekarno–Hatta airport to start your journey to the sunrise capital, TOKYO.        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 2: ARRIVAL - TOKYO CITY TOUR</strong>\r\n        <p>Early in the morning in Tokyo, you will visit ASAKUSA KANON TEMPLE, one of the temples in Japan and shop along NAKAMISE STREET, where you can try various kinds of Japanese snacks. You will then be invited to take pictures at TOKYO SKY TREE, IMPERIAL PALACE and TOKYO TOWER. Then you will be invited to take pictures at HACHIKO STATUE, the famous loyal dog statue and shop around the SHIBUYA area (L/D)\r\nHotel: Metropolitan Tokyo (*4) or similar\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 3: TOKYO DISNEYLAND</strong>\r\n        <p>After breakfast, you will be invited to visit TOKYO DISNEYLAND which is the first Disneyland in Asia with the world famous cartoon character, Mickey Mouse, Donald Duck. Don\'t forget the interesting attractions and games in Tommorow Land, Fantasy Land, Adventure Land and others. (B,L,D)\r\nHotel: Metropolitan Tokyo (*4) or similar\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 4 : TOKYO DISNEYSEA - KAWAGUCHI</strong>\r\n        <p>Today you will visit TOKYO DISNEYSEA , a place where you can enjoy attractions and games in Tower of Terror, Mysterious Island, Mermaid Lagoon, Lost River Delta. Then you will continue your journey to KAWAGUCHI (B,L,D)\r\nHotel: Jiragono Fujino Yakata (4*) or similar\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 5: KAWAGUCHI –HAMAMATSU- TOYOHASHI</strong>\r\n        <p>Today you head to MT FUJI, the highest mountain in Japan (weather permitting, you will be able to climb to level 5). After that you will be escorted to the station to try the experience of riding a typical Japanese bullet train (Shinkansen) to TOYOHASHI city (B,L,D)\r\nHotel : Loisir Hotel (4*) or similar\r\n</p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 6 : TOYOHASHI - KYOTO – OSAKA</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n				In the morning, you will continue your journey to the former capital of Japan, KYOTO City. Upon arrival, you will be invited for a city tour by visiting FUSHIMI INARI, a Shinto shrine which has more than 10,000 red/orange and black tori (gates) and then KIYOMIZU TEMPLE, one of the famous temples in Kyoto and a UNESCO world cultural heritage. The journey continues to OSAKA City by bus which is the second largest city in Japan. You will shop at SHINSAIBASHI SHOPPING STREET, one of the famous shopping centers in the city (B,L,D)\r\nHotel : Sheraton Miyako (4*) or similar\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 7 : OSAKA</strong>\r\n        <p>After breakfast, you will be transferred to UNIVERSAL STUDIOS THEME PARK, Asia\'s first and newest film and television production studio. Next, you will be invited to see the crowds in the SHINSAIBASHI SHOPPING STREET shopping area. (B,L)\r\nHotel : Sheraton Miyako (4*) or similar\r\n</p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 8 : KANSAI – JAKARTA</strong>\r\n        <p>Today you will be transferred to the airport for your flight back to Jakarta. Thank you for your participation and see you at another travel destinations. (MP)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', 'JAPAN GOLDEN ROUTE 8D', 'JAPAN GOLDEN ROUTE 8D-English'),
(18, 'JAPAN SHIRAKAWA-GO 7D', 'Jepang', '7', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Iyashi No Sato </strong>\r\n        <p>\r\nadalah sebuah desa yang berdiri di lokasi bekas desa pertanian di tepi barat Danau Saiko. Jika Anda menapakan kaki di Desa ini, Anda akan merasakan ketenangan dan kedamaian. Lokasinya pas sekali untuk menenangkan diri di sela kesibukan. Anda dapat bersantai atau berjalan pelan mengelilingi desa. Di sini terdapat rumah-rumah beratap jerami tradisional desa, dan dibuka sebagai museum terbuka dan desa kerajinan tradisional dimana orang dapat belajar tentang budaya dan mencoba dan membeli berbagai kerajinan lokal\r\n\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n   \r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 01: JAKARTA – NARITA</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Berkumpul di bandara Soekarno–Hatta untuk memulai perjalanan Anda menuju Tokyo.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 02: ARRIVAL - TOKYO CITY TOUR</strong>\r\n        <p>Pagi hari tiba di Tokyo, Anda akan mengunjungi ASAKUSA KANON TEMPLE salah satu kuil di jepang dan berbelanja di sepanjang NAKAMISE STREET, dimana Anda dapat mencoba berbagai macam makanan ringan khas Jepang.   Anda kemudian akan diajak berfoto di TOKYO SKY TREE, IMPERIAL PALACE dan TOKYO TOWER. Kemudian Anda akan diajak untuk berfoto di  HACHIKO STATUE, patung anjing setia yang terkenal  dan berbelanja di sekitar daerah SHIBUYA  (MS,MM)\r\nHotel: Metropolitan Tokyo (*4)  atau setaraf\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 03:  TOKYO – YAMANASHI</strong>\r\n        <p>Setelah santap pagi, anda akan diantar menuju MT. FUJI (jika cuaca memungkinkan, Anda akan dapat naik sampai tingkat 5th Station).  Selanjutnya anda akan berbelanja di GOTEMBA OUTLET. Kemudian Anda akan diantar menuju Lake Kawaguchi District (Onsen) untuk bermalam. (MP,MS,MM)\r\nHotel : Lake Kawaguchi Onsen (4*) atau kota terdekat\r\n\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 04: YAMANASHI – TAKAYAMA</strong>\r\n        <p>Setelah makan pagi, Anda akan mengunjungi IYASHI NO SATO (HEALING VILLAGE), sebuah desa tradisional Jepang dimana Anda dapat melihat rumah dan bangunan tradisional dengan jerami dan anyaman bamboo sebagdan dindingnnya, HIRAYU FALLS , SANOMACHI STREET dan TAKAYAMA. (MP,MS,MM)\r\n   Hotel : Hida Plaza (4*) atau setaraf\r\n\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 05: TAKAYAMA – SHIRAKAWAGO – KYOTO </strong>\r\n        <p>Hari ini anda akan diajak ke situs warisan dunia UNESCO terpopuler di Jepang, SHIRAKAWA-GO GASSHO VILLAGE. Setelahnya, Anda akan mengunjungi  KIYOMIZU TEMPLE, salah satu kuil terkenal di Kyoto dan merupakan warisan budaya dunia UNESCO (MP,MS,MM)\r\nHotel: Ibis Style Kyoto (4*) atau kota terdekat \r\n\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 06: KYOTO – OSAKA</strong>\r\n        <p>Setelah makan pagi, Anda akan diantar mengunjungi FUSHIMI INARI, kuil Shinto memiliki lebih dari 10.000 tori (gerbang) berwarna merah/orange dan hitam, KINKAKU-JI TEMPLE, dan OSAKA CASTLE. Lalu Anda akan berbelanja di SHINSAIBASHI SHOPPING STREET.  (MP,MS,MM)\r\nHotel : Richmond Osaka (4*) atau setaraf \r\n\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 07: OSAKA – JAKARTA</strong>\r\n        <p>Hari ini Anda akan diantar ke airport untuk penerbangan kembali ke Jakarta.  Terima kasih atas partisipasi Anda dan sampai jumpa di acara perjalanan yang lainnya. (MP) \r\n\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', 'japan11.png', 'japan9.png', 'japan3.png', 'Mancanegara', '5', 'japan7.png', NULL, NULL, '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Iyashi No Sato </strong>\r\n        <p>\r\nis a village that stands on the site of a former farming village on the west bank of Lake Saiko. If you set foot in this village, you will feel serenity and peace. The location is perfect for calming down on the sidelines of busyness. You can relax or take a slow walk around the village. Here are the village\'s traditional thatched roof houses, and opened as an open-air museum and traditional crafts village where people can learn about the culture and try and buy various local crafts.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n   \r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 01: JAKARTA – NARITA</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n					Gather at Soekarno–Hatta airport to start your journey to Tokyo.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 02: ARRIVAL - TOKYO CITY TOUR</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n				Early in the morning in Tokyo, you will visit ASAKUSA KANON TEMPLE, one of the temples in Japan and shop along NAKAMISE STREET, where you can try various kinds of Japanese snacks. You will then be invited to take pictures at TOKYO SKY TREE, IMPERIAL PALACE and TOKYO TOWER. Then you will be invited to take pictures at HACHIKO STATUE, the famous loyal dog statue and shop around the SHIBUYA area (L,D)\r\nHotel: Metropolitan Tokyo (*4) or similar\r\n		</p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 03: TOKYO – YAMANASHI</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n				After breakfast, you will be escorted to MT. FUJI (weather permitting, you will be able to go up to level 5th Station). Next you will shop at GOTEMBA OUTLET. Then you will be transferred to Lake Kawaguchi District (Onsen) for overnight. (B,L,D)\r\nHotel : Lake Kawaguchi Onsen (4*) or the nearest town\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 04: YAMANASHI – TAKAYAMA</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n				After breakfast, you will visit IYASHI NO SATO (HEALING VILLAGE),  a traditional Japanese village where you can see traditional houses and buildings with thatched and woven bamboo as walls, HIRAYU FALLS , SANOMACHI STREET and TAKAYAMA. (MP, MS, MM)\r\n Hotel : Hida Plaza (4*) or similar\r\n\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 05: TAKAYAMA – SHIRAKAWAGO – KYOTO</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n				Today you will be taken to the most popular UNESCO world heritage site in Japan, SHIRAKAWA-GO GASSHO VILLAGE. After that, you will visit KIYOMIZU TEMPLE, one of the famous temples in Kyoto and a UNESCO world cultural heritage (B,L,D)\r\nHotel: Ibis Style Kyoto (4*) or the nearest city\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 06: KYOTO – OSAKA</strong>\r\n        <p>After breakfast, you will be escorted to FUSHIMI INARI, a Shinto shrine with more than 10,000 red/orange and black tori (gates), KINKAKU-JI TEMPLE, and OSAKA CASTLE. Then you will shop at SHINSAIBASHI SHOPPING STREET. (B,L,D)\r\nHotel : Richmond Osaka (4*) or similar\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 07: OSAKA – JAKARTA</strong>\r\n        <p>Today you will be transferred to the airport for your flight back to Jakarta. Thank you for your participation and see you at another travel destinations. (B)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', 'JAPAN SHIRAKAWA-GO 7D', 'Itin JAPAN SHIRAKAWA-GO 7D- English'),
(19, 'KUALA LUMPUR–GENTING 4D', 'Malaysia', '4', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Menara Petronas, atau Menara Kembar Petronas</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Merupakan gedung pencakar langit kembar di Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. Menara Petronas tetap menjadi menara kembar tertinggi di dunia.  Twin Tower adalah landmark utama Kuala Lumpur.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Genting Casino</strong>\r\n        <p>adalah salah satu tempat aktivitas malam paling populer di Genting Highlands, di mana Anda dapat menguji keberuntungan Anda dalam memenangkan pembayaran besar-besaran.      Sky casino adalah casino terbaru di Genting Highlands.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Genting Highlands atau Tanah Tinggi Genting (2000 m di atas muka laut)</strong>\r\n        <p>adalah puncak gunung dari pegunungan Titiwangsa di negara bagian Pahang dan Selangor, tempat ini dapat dicapai dengan satu jam berkendara roda empat dari Kuala Lumpur atau melalui kereta gantung Genting Skyway yang saat ini merupakan yang tercepat di dunia dan terpanjang di Asia Tenggara).<br> Genting Highlands didirikan oleh Lim Goh Tong dari Fujian, Cina pada awal tahun 1960-an. Sejak itu, Genting Highlands berkembang pesat dan menjadi salah satu tujuan wisaterkenal di Malaysia	\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>	\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 01: JAKARTA – KUALA LUMPUR </strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Pada waktu yang telah ditentukan, Anda berkumpul di Bandara Internasional Soekarno-Hatta untuk memulai perjalanan menuju Kuala Lumpur. Setibanya Anda akan city tour dengan mengunjungi / melewati: King\'s Palace, Independence Square, National Monument, KL Tower & Petronas Twin Tower (photo stop), Parliament House, mengunjungi Batu Cave, sebuah bukit kapur, yang memiliki serangkaian gua dan kuil gua . Kemudian Anda akan menuju Genting. Setibanya, acara bebas yang dapat Anda nikmati dengan berbelanja di beberapa factory outlet ataupun mengadu keberuntungan di kasino (MS,MM)\r\nHotel: First World atau setaraf (4*)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 02: GENTING </strong>\r\n        <p>Setelah makan pagi, hari ini acara bebas seharian yang dapat Anda pergunakan untuk berbelanja ataupun kembali mengadu keberuntungan Anda di kasino (MP)\r\nHotel: First World atau setaraf (4*)\r\n\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 03: GENTING – KUALA  LUMPUR  </strong>\r\n        <p>Hari ini Anda akan menuju Kuala Lumpur kembali. Setibanya, Anda akan berbelanja di Sungei Wang Plaza, Petaling Street dan Central Market  (MP,MS,MM)\r\nHotel: Federal Hotel atau setaraf (4*)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 04: KUALA  LUMPUR  - JAKARTA</strong>\r\n        <p>Hari ini Anda akan diantar ke airport untuk penerbangan kembali ke Jakarta. Terima kasih atas kepercayaan Anda kepada kami. Sampai jumpa pada acara perjalanan yang lainnya (MP)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    \r\n</ul>', 'kl1.png', 'kl2.png', 'kl3.png', 'Mancanegara', '5', 'kl4.png', NULL, NULL, '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>The Petronas Towers, or Petronas Twin Towers</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        are twin skyscrapers in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. The Petronas Towers remain the tallest twin towers in the world. Twin Tower is Kuala Lumpur\'s main landmark.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Genting Casino</strong>\r\n        <p>is one of the most popular nightlife venues in Genting Highlands, where you can test your luck in winning big payouts. Sky casino is the newest casino in Genting Highlands.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Genting Highlands (2000 m above sea level)</strong>\r\n        <p>is the mountain peak of the Titiwangsa mountains in the states of Pahang and Selangor, it can be reached by a one-hour four-wheel drive from Kuala Lumpur or via the Genting Skyway cable car which is currently is the fastest in the world and the longest in Southeast Asia).\r\n<br> Genting Highlands was founded by Lim Goh Tong from Fujian, China in the early 1960s. Since then, Genting Highlands has grown rapidly and has become one of the most famous tourist destinations in Malaysia\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>	\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 01: JAKARTA – KUALA LUMPUR </strong>\r\n       At the appointed time, you will gather at Soekarno-Hatta International Airport to start your journey to Kuala Lumpur. Upon arrival you will have a city tour by visiting/passing: King\'s Palace, Independence Square, National Monument, KL Tower & Petronas Twin Tower (photo stop), Parliament House, visiting Batu Cave, a limestone hill, which has a series of caves and cave temples. Then you will head to Genting. Upon arrival, free program that you can enjoy by shopping at several factory outlets or try your luck at the casino (L,D)\r\nHotel: First World or similar (4*)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 02: GENTING </strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n				After breakfast, today is a free day all day that you can use for shopping or try your luck again at the casino (B)\r\nHotel: First World or similar  (4*)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 03: GENTING – KUALA  LUMPUR  </strong>\r\n        <p>Today you will return to Kuala Lumpur. Upon arrival, you will shop at Sungei Wang Plaza, Petaling Street and Central Market (B,L,D)\r\nHotel: Federal Hotel or similar  (4*)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 04: KUALA  LUMPUR  - JAKARTA</strong>\r\n        <p>Today you will be transferred to the airport for your flight back to Jakarta. Thank you for your trust in us. See you on another travel destinations (B)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    \r\n</ul>', 'KUL-Genting 4D', 'Itin KUALA LUMPUR 4D-English'),
(21, 'SINGAPORE TRIP 4D', 'Singapore', '4', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>The Merlion</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        The Merlion adalah maskot resmi Singapura, digambarkan sebagai makhluk mitos dengan kepala singa dan tubuh ikan. <br>\r\n				Merlion pertama kali digunakan di Singapura sebagai logo dewan pariwisata. Namanya menggabungkan \"mer\", yang berarti laut, dan \"singa\". Tubuh ikan melambangkan asal Singapura sebagai desa nelayan,. Kepala singa melambangkan nama asli Singapura—Singapura—yang berarti \"kota singa\" atau \"kota singa\". Simbol ini dirancang oleh Alec Fraser-Brunner, anggota Komite Souvenir dan kurator Van Kleef Aquarium yang digunakan mulai 26 Maret 1964 \r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Marina Bay Sands</strong>\r\n        <p>Marina Bay Sands adalah pusat hiburan terpadu, menghadap ke Teluk Marina di Singapura. Dikembangkan oleh Las Vegas Sands merupakan investasi tunggal paling mahal di dunia. <br>\r\n				Tempat wisata ini memiliki 2.561 kamar hotel, ruang pameran dan pertemuan seluas 120.000m², mal The Shoppes dan ArtScience Museum, Sands Theatre dan Grand Theatre, tujuh restoran koki selebriti, dua pavilyun mengambang, kasino dengan lebih dari 600 meja judi dan 1.500 mesin jakpot. Kompleks ini dinaungi Sands SkyPark sepanjang 340 meter dengan kapasitas 3.900 orang dan kolam renang tanpa batas (infinity edge) sepanjang 150 meter, yang merupakan ruang menggantung terbesar di dunia dengan kantilever sejauh 67 meter di menara utara \r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Gardens by the Bay</strong>\r\n        <p>Gardens by the Bay adalah taman alam seluas 101 hektar (250 acre) di Wilayah Tengah Singapura, Flower Dome-nya adalah rumah kaca kaca terbesar di dunia. <br> Gardens by the Bay adalah bagian dari rencana negara untuk mengubah \"Kota Taman\" menjadi \"Kota di dalam Taman\", dengan tujuan meningkatkan kualitas hidup dengan meningkatkan tanaman hijau dan flora di kota.  Saat ini menjadi objek wisata populer di Singapura\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>	\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 01: JAKARTA – SINGAPORE</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Berkumpul di Bandara Soekarno–Hatta untuk memulai perjalanan menuju Singapore. Setibanya Anda akan diantar city tour mengunjungi/melewati Merlion Park, dimana patung yang berbentuk bagian dari kepala singa dan badan ikan yang juga merupakan landmark kota ini berada, mengunjungi Garden by the bay, sebuah taman alam seluas lebih dari 100 hektar. Kemudian Anda akan berbelanja \r\ndi Orchard Road, pusat perbelanjaan terkenal di kota ini. (MS)\r\nHotel: Dorsett Chinatown atau setaraf (*4)\r\n\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 02: MARINA BAY SANDS SINGAPORE </strong>\r\n        <p>Setelah makan pagi, Anda dapat menguji keberuntungan Anda di Casino Marina Bay Sands (MP)\r\nHotel: Dorsett Chinatown atau setaraf (*4)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 03: SINGAPORE UNIVERSAL STUDIO (MP/MS-COUPON)  </strong>\r\n        <p>Acara hari ini Anda akan bermain di Universal Studios Singapore. Anda akan menikmati seharian berkeliling USS yang menawarkan banyak hal untuk memenuhi imajinasi Anda, apakah itu berfoto dengan tokoh-tokoh dari film-film blockbuster Hollywood seperti Shrek®, Madagascar ataupun Kung Fu Panda, Malam harinya Anda juga akan diajak menikmati Song of the Sea, pertunjukan laser dan air yang spektakuler u ntuk keluarga (MP,MS kupon)\r\nHotel: Dorsett Chinatown atau setaraf (*4)\r\n\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>HARI 04: SINGAPORE – JAKARTA </strong>\r\n        <p>Hari ini Anda akan diantar ke airport untuk penerbangan kembali ke Jakarta yang juga merupakan akhir dari acara perjalanan Anda kali ini. Terima kasih atas kepercayaan Anda, sampai jumpa pada acara perjalanan yang lainnya.(MP) \r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    \r\n</ul>', 'sing1.png', 'sing2.png', 'sing3.png', 'Mancanegara', '5', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>The Merlion</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        The Merlion is Singapore\'s official mascot, depicted as a mythical creature with the head of a lion and the body of a fish.<br>\r\n				The Merlion was first used in Singapore as a tourism board logo. Its name combines \"mer\", which means sea, and \"lion\". The fish body symbolizes Singapore\'s origin as a fishing village. The lion\'s head represents Singapore\'s original name—Singapore—which means \"city of lions\" or \"city of lions\". This symbol was designed by Alec Fraser-Brunner, member of the Souvenirs Committee and curator of the Van Kleef Aquarium which was used from 26 March 1964\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Marina Bay Sands</strong>\r\n        <p>is an integrated entertainment centre, overlooking Marina Bay in Singapore. Developed by Las Vegas Sands it is the single most expensive investment in the world.<br>\r\n				This tourist spot has 2,561 hotel rooms, 120,000m² of exhibition and meeting space, The Shoppes mall and ArtScience Museum, Sands Theater and Grand Theatre, seven celebrity chef restaurants, two floating pavilions, a casino with more than 600 gambling tables and 1,500 jackpot machines. The complex is home to the 340-meter-long Sands SkyPark with a capacity of 3,900 people and a 150-meter-long infinity edge pool, which is the world\'s largest hanging space with a 67-meter cantilever in the north tower.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Gardens by the Bay</strong>\r\n        <p>Gardens by the Bay is a 101 hectare (250 acre) nature park in the Central Region of Singapore, its Flower Dome is the largest glass greenhouse in the world.<br> Gardens by the Bay is part of the state\'s plan to turn a \"Garden City\" into a \"City within a Garden\", with the aim of improving the quality of life by increasing the greenery and flora in the city. Currently a popular tourist attraction in Singapore\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>	\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 01: JAKARTA – SINGAPORE</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n       Gather at Soekarno–Hatta Airport to start the journey to Singapore. Upon arrival, you will be escorted to a city tour visiting/passing the Merlion Park, where the statue shaped part of a lion\'s head and fish body which is also a landmark of the city is located, visiting Garden by the bay, a natural park covering an area of ​​more than 100 hectares. Then you will shop on Orchard Road, the city\'s famous shopping center. (B)\r\nHotel: Dorsett Chinatown or similar\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 02: MARINA BAY SANDS SINGAPORE </strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n				After breakfast, you can test your luck at Casino Marina Bay Sands (B)\r\nHotel: Dorsett Chinatown or similar (*4)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 03: SINGAPORE UNIVERSAL STUDIO (MP/MS-COUPON)  </strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n				Today\'s event you will play at Universal Studios Singapore. You will enjoy a day touring the USS which offers many things to fulfill your imagination, whether it\'s taking pictures with characters from Hollywood blockbusters such as Shrek®, Madagascar or Kung Fu Panda, in the evening you will also be invited to enjoy Song of the Sea, spectacular laser and water show for family (B,L coupons)\r\nHotel: Dorsett Chinatown or similar (*4)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>DAY 04: SINGAPORE – JAKARTA </strong>\r\n        <p>Today you will be transferred to the airport for your flight back to Jakarta which is also the end of your trip this time. Thank you for your trust, see you on another travel destinationst.(B)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    \r\n</ul>', 'SIN 4D', 'itin SINGAPORE TRIP 4D-English');
