(31, 'KOREA MUSLIM TOUR  5D', 'Korea', '5', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Masjid Itaewon</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        dikenal juga dengan nama Masjid Seoul Central  terletak di daerah Itaewon, Seoul, Korea Selatan. Selain pusat wisata kuliner, Itaewon juga menjadi lokasi masjid tertua ini. <br>\r\n        Seoul Central Mosque dibuka sejak tahun 1976 dan tepatnya berlokasi di Hannam-dong, Distrik Yongsan.\r\n        Saat pertama kali didirikan atas inisiasi Korean Muslim Federation .masjid ini hanya didatangi oleh sekitar 3.000 umat Muslim di Korea Selatan setiap tahunnya dari berbagai Negara seperti  Pakistan, Bangladesh, hingga Indonesia. <br>\r\n        Masjid ini dibangun tiga lantai. Lantai bawah untuk kantor administrasi, lantai dua untuk ibadah pria, dan lantai tiga untuk ibadah wanita.\r\n\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Nami Island</strong>\r\n        <p>pulau dengan pohon-pohonnya yang khas memang terlihat sangat indah dan romantis terletak di area Bendungan Cheongpyeong, di wilayah Chuncheon-si, Gangwon-do. Pulau mungil berdiameter 6 kilometer dan luas area sekitar 460.000 m2 ini, berbentuk setengah lingkaran atau seperti sebuah mangkok. <br>\r\n        Nami Island sendiri memperoleh namanya yang diambil dari nama salah satu pahlawan Korea Selatan, yaitu Jenderal Nami. Makam sang jederal juga berada di pulau ini. Namun nama pulau ini menjadi semakin populer sebagai objek wisata setelah digunakan untuk shooting serial drama “Winter Sonata” yang dibintangi Bae Yong-jun dan Choi Ji-woo.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Istana Gyeongbok</strong>\r\n        <p>adalah istana kerajaan utama dari dinasti Joseon. Dibangun pada tahun 1395, terletak di utara Seoul, Korea Selatan.  Istana ini termasuk dari lima istana besar dan merupakan yang terbesar yang dibangun oleh Dinasti Joseon.\r\n        <br>\r\n        Istana Gyeongbok saat ini dibuka untuk umum dan Museum Nasional Rakyat Korea (National Folk Museum of Korea) berdiri di dalamnya.\r\n\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Kampung Hanok Bukchon</strong>\r\n        <p>adalah sebuah kampung rumah tradisional Korea di Seoul, Korea Selatan.\r\n        Kampung Hanok Bukchon memiliki lorong-lorong yang sempit dan menampilkan suasana kota Seoul pada masa lalu. Rumah-rumah para bangsawan di kampung ini masih terpelihara dengan baik, dan beberapa di antaranya menawarkan penginapan bagi wisatawan yang ingin merasakan pengalaman kehidupan tradisional Korea\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>  <strong>Paket sudah termasuk:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>Tiket International Jakarta-Incheon PP by Garuda Indonesia/ Asiana Airlines  Economy termasuk taxes internasional (Tiket Grup Fixed Date & No Extend)</li>\r\n    <li>Bagasi sesuai dengan ketentuan Airlines 30kg</li>\r\n    <li>Akomodasi hotel  setaraf  *4  (Twin / Triple)</li>\r\n    <li>Transportasi bus Pariwisata & tiket masuk objek wisata</li>\r\n    <li>Acara Tour & makan sesuai program paket tour diatas</li>\r\n    <li>Mineral Water 01 Botol Perhari</li>\r\n    <li>Tour Leader (minimal 20 pax)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<strong>Paket tidak termasuk:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>Visa Korea Individual</li>\r\n    <li>Tipping Tour Guide & Driver</li>\r\n    <li>Asuransi perjalanan</li>\r\n    <li>Simcard Internet (optional)</li>\r\n    <li>Tipping Porter Hotel, Minibar, Laundry, Telp, Kelebihan Bagasi dsb</li>\r\n</ol>', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Hari 01: JAKARTA – INCHEON </strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Malam ini kita berkumpul di Bandara Soekarno-Hatta untuk berangkat menuju ke Incheon dengan Garuda Indonesia / Asiana.  Bermalam di PESAWAT     \r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Hari 02: INCHEON – SONGDO – ANSAN </strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Setibanya sampai di Incheon disambut oleh Guide yang ramah kemudian pergi mengunjungi Songdo Central Park yang merupakan tempat syuting “Running Man” acara variety show Korea yang terkenal. Setelah itu akan dianjutkan dengan menuju ke Ansan, disini kita akan mengunjungi  Bada Hyanggi Theme Park, Nojeckbong Fall Park, dan yang terakhir dilanjutkan dengan Ansan Mosque, shalat di sini. Setelah itu ke Seoul N-Tower love and lock. Lalu Check in di hotel untuk beristirahat. (B,L,D)\r\n        Bermalam di CS PREMIER Hotel ****Local / similar\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Hari 03 : NAMI ISLAND – SEOUL </strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Sarapan pagi di hotel. Lalu, kita mengunjungi Nami Island, yang merupakan tempat syuting film Winter Sonata. Disana kita akan belajar membuat kimchi dan mencoba menggunakan Hanbok (Baju Tradisional Korea). Selanjutnya akan dilanjutkan dengan pergi ke ITAEWON MOSQUE untuk beribadah. Hari ini juga kita akan pergi ke Bukchon Hanok Village yang dimana kita dapat menikmati perumahan tradisional. Terakhir akan dibawa ke tempat pusat berbelanja untuk shopping yaitu di Dongdaemun. (B,L,D)\r\n        Bermalam di CS PREMIER Hotel ****Local / similar\r\n        SHALAT DI ITAEWON MOSQUE\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Hari 04 : SEOUL CITY TOUR </strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Sarapan pagi di hotel. Pada hari ini kita akan melewati Blue House, kemudian mengunjungi Gyeongbok Palace & National Folkfore Museum. Hari ini juga kita akan mengintip rahasia kecantikan orang Korea dan berbelanja di UGB Cosmetic Shop, Amethyst Showcase, National Ginseng Museum, Red Pine Shop (Korea Herbal Medicine), Duty Free Shop (Belanja murah bebas pajak), dan shopping di Myeongdong Street. (B,L,D)\r\n        Bermalam di CS PREMIER Hotel ****Local / similar\r\n        SHALAT DI MUSHOLLA K-STYLE HUB BUILDING\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Hari 05 : SEOUL – JAKARTA </strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Morning call di pagi hari setelah itu kita akan berangkat untuk sarapan Udon dan Berbelanja oleh-oleh di Chungha Grocery Shop sebelum kita ke Incheon Airport. Tiba waktunya diantar ke Airport untuk kembali ke Jakarta, dan sampai jumpa di tour selanjutnya bersama kami. (B)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>    \r\n</ul>', 'kmuslim1.png', 'kmuslim2.png', 'kmuslim3.png', 'muslim', '5', 'kmuslim4.png', NULL, NULL, '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Itaewon Mosque</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        also known as Seoul Central Mosque is located in Itaewon area, Seoul, South Korea. In addition to the culinary tourism center, Itaewon is also the location of this oldest mosque.\r\n        <br>\r\n        Seoul Central Mosque was opened in 1976 and is precisely located in Hannam-dong, Yongsan District.\r\n        When it was first established at the initiation of the Korean Muslim Federation, this mosque is only visited by about 3,000 Muslims in South Korea every year from various countries such as Pakistan, Bangladesh, to Indonesia.\r\n        The mosque was built three floors. The lower floor is for administrative offices, the second floor is for men\'s worship, and the third floor is for women\'s worship.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Nami Island</strong>\r\n        <p>an island with its distinctive trees does look very beautiful and romantic, located in the Cheongpyeong Dam area, in the Chuncheon-si area, Gangwon-do. This tiny island with a diameter of 6 kilometers and an area of ​​about 460,000 m2 is semicircular or like a bowl.<br>\r\n        Nami Island itself got its name from the name of one of the heroes of South Korea, namely General Nami. The tomb of the general is also on this island. However, the name of this island became increasingly popular as a tourist attraction after being used for shooting the drama series \"Winter Sonata\" starring Bae Yong-jun and Choi Ji-woo.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Gyeongbok Palace</strong>\r\n        <p>was the main royal palace of the Joseon dynasty. Built in 1395, it is located north of Seoul, South Korea. This palace is one of the five great palaces and is the largest built by the Joseon Dynasty.\r\n        <br>\r\n        Gyeongbok Palace is currently open to the public and the National Folk Museum of Korea is located inside.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Bukchon Hanok Village</strong>\r\n        <p>is a traditional Korean house village in Seoul, South Korea.\r\n        Bukchon Hanok Village has narrow alleys and displays the atmosphere of the old Seoul city. The houses of the nobles in this village are still well-preserved, and some of them offer accommodation for tourists who want to experience traditional Korean life\r\n\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul> <strong>Package included:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>International Jakarta-Incheon PP by Garuda Indonesia/ Asiana Airlines Economy ticket including international taxes (Fixed Date & No Extend Group Ticket)</li>\r\n    <li>Baggage according to Airline 30kg</li>\r\n    <li>Hotel accommodation *4  (Twin / Triple)</li>\r\n    <li>Tourist bus transportation & attraction entrance tickets</li>\r\n    <li>Tour & meal events according to the tour package program above</li>\r\n    <li>Mineral Water 01 Bottles per day</li>\r\n    <li>Tour Leader (minimum 20 pax)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<strong>Package Excluded:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>Individual Korean Visa</li>\r\n    <li>Tipping Tour Guide & Driver</li>\r\n    <li>Insurance</li>\r\n    <li>Internet sim card (optional)</li>\r\n    <li>Tipping Porter Hotel, Minibar, Laundry, Phone, Excess Baggage etc</li>\r\n</ol>', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Day 01: JAKARTA – INCHEON</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Tonight we gather at Soekarno-Hatta Airport to go to Incheon with Garuda Indonesia / Asiana. Overnight on the flight.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Day 02: INCHEON – SONGDO – ANSAN</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Upon arrival in Incheon, they were greeted by a friendly guide and then went to visit Songdo Central Park, which is the shooting location for the famous Korean variety show \"Running Man\". After that, we will continue by heading to Ansan, here we will visit Bada Hyanggi Theme Park, Nojeckbong Fall Park, and finally continue with Ansan Mosque, pray here. After that go to Seoul N-Tower love and lock. Then check in at the hotel to rest. (B,L,D)\r\n        Overnight at CS PREMIER Hotel ****Local / similar\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Day 03 : NAMI ISLAND – SEOUL</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Breakfast at the hotel. Then, we visited Nami Island, which was the shooting location for the film Winter Sonata. There we will learn to make kimchi and try to use Hanbok (Korean Traditional Dress). Then it will be continued by going to ITAEWON MOSQUE to worship. Today we will also go to Bukchon Hanok Village where we can enjoy traditional housing. Finally, you will be taken to a shopping center for shopping, namely in Dongdaemun. (B,L,D)\r\n        Overnight at CS PREMIER Hotel ****Local / similar\r\n        PRAYER AT ITAEWON MOSQUE\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Day 04 : SEOUL CITY TOUR</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Breakfast at the hotel. On this day we will pass the Blue House, then visit Gyeongbok Palace & National Folkfore Museum. Today we will also take a peek at Korean beauty secrets and shop at UGB Cosmetic Shop, Amethyst Showcase, National Ginseng Museum, Red Pine Shop (Korea Herbal Medicine), Duty Free Shop (Cheap shopping tax free), and shopping at Myeongdong Street. (B,L,D)\r\n        Overnight at CS PREMIER Hotel ****Local / similar\r\n        PRAYER IN MUSHOLLA K-STYLE HUB BUILDING\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Day 05 : SEOUL – JAKARTA</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Morning call in the morning after that we will leave for Udon breakfast and shop for souvenirs at Chungha Grocery Shop before we head to Incheon Airport. It\'s time to transfer to the airport to return to Jakarta, and see you on the next tour with us. (B)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>    \r\n</ul>', 'KOREA MUSLIM 5 HARI', 'KOREA MUSLIM TOUR  5D - English'),
(32, 'HONGKONG SHENZHEN MUSLIM TOUR 4D', 'Hongkong', '4', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Masjid Kowloon</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Masjid ini termasuk masjid terbesar yang ada di Hong Kong karna mampu menampung sekitar 3.500 orang. Selain untuk menunaikan ibadah, Masjid Kowloon juga memiliki dua Madrasah untuk anak laki-laki dan perempuan. Selain itu, di sini juga terdapat Kelas Dakwah (Intermediate Course on Islam) untuk non-Muslim yang diselenggarakan secara rutin setiap minggu di masjid ini.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Masjid Chai Wan</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Masjid yang dibuka pertama kali pada tahun 1963 ini merupakan masjid ke lima yang ada di Hong Kong. Kegiatan beribadah  sering diadakan di masjid ini, tidak hanya sebagai tempat beribadah saja, di Masjid Chai Wan juga terdapat Madrasah yang di khususkan untuk anak-anak yang ingin belajar Al-Quran. Selain itu masjid ini juga berada tepat di area yang sunyi dan dikelilingi oleh pemandangan hijau yang membuat ibadah para umat muslim menjadi semakin khusyuk.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Masjid Jamiah</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Masjid Jamiah merupakan masjid pertama yang ada di Hong Kong, masjid ini dibangun pada tahun 1840-an, dianggap sebagai salah satu bangunan bersejarah oleh pemerintah Hong Kong. Seperti masjid pada umumnya, sholat lima waktu rutin diadakan di tempat ini, termasuk sholat taraweh saat bulan Ramadan. Selain itu, saat bulan ramadhan tiba, Masjid Jamia juga turut menyediakan menu sahur dan berbuka bagi umat muslim yang berpuasa.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Hari 01: JAKARTA – HONGKONG – ZHUHAI </strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Hari ini Anda berkumpul di Bandara Soekarno Hatta untuk terbang menuju Hongkong. Setibanya di Hongkong kita akan ke Hongkong city tour mengunjungi Garden Of Star & Starry Gallery, Victoria Peak (mid level exclude tram) dimana Anda bisa melihat pemandangan kota Hongkong dan semenanjung Kowloon, dan mengunjungi Masjid Jiansazui .Shopping stop di Toko Coklat dan Jc Jewerly Workshop. Lalu kita akan menuju ke Zhuhai via New Bridge jembatan laut terpanjang di dunia. Sesampainya Anda akan makan malam, lalu check-in hotel (L,D)   \r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Hari 02: ZHUHAI – SHENZHEN</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Sarapan pagi di hotel. City tour Zhuhai mengunjungi The Lovers Road, Fishing Girl Statue. Perjalanan dilanjutkan menuju ke Shenzhen mengunjungi Netherland Flower Town, Masjid Meilin, Herbal Shop, Jade Shop, Shenzhen Light Show, dan shopping di Dongmen Street (B,L,D)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Hari 03: SHENZHEN– HONGKONG</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Hari ini setelah sarapan pagi di hotel, anda bisa berbelanja atau berfoto di sekitar hotel. Sampai waktunya Anda akan diantar menuju Hongkong. Setibanya Anda akan mengunjungi Masjid Kowloon dan Masjid Jamiah. Kemudian Anda akan berbelanja di shopping centre Hongkong (B,LD)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Hari 04 : HONGKONG – JAKARTA</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Hari ini Anda akan diantar ke airport untuk penerbangan kembali ke Jakarta.  Terima kasih atas partisipasi Anda dan sampai jumpa di acara perjalanan yang lainnya. (B) \r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', 'hongkong1.png', 'hongkong2.png', 'hongkong3.png', 'muslim', '5', 'hongkong4.png', NULL, NULL, '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Kowloon Mosque</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        This mosque is one of the largest mosques in Hong Kong because it can accommodate about 3,500 people. In addition to performing worship, the Kowloon Mosque also has two Madrasas for boys and girls. In addition, here there is also an Intermediate Course on Islam for non-Muslims which is held regularly every week at this mosque.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Chai Wan Mosque</strong>\r\n        <p>The mosque which was first opened in 1963 is the fifth mosque in Hong Kong. Worship activities are often held at this mosque, not only as a place of worship, at Chai Wan Mosque there is also a Madrasa which is dedicated to children who want to learn the Koran. In addition, this mosque is also located right in a quiet area and surrounded by green scenery which makes the worship of Muslims more solemn.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Jamiah Mosque</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\n        Jamiah Mosque is the first mosque in Hong Kong, this mosque was built in the 1840s, is considered one of the historic buildings by the Hong Kong government. Like mosques in general, the five daily prayers are regularly held in this place, including the Taraweeh prayers during the month of Ramadan. In addition, when the month of Ramadan arrives, the Jamia Mosque also provides a menu for sahur and iftar for fasting Muslims.\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', '<ul>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Day 01: JAKARTA – HONGKONG – ZHUHAI</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\nToday you gather at Soekarno Hatta Airport to fly to Hong Kong. Arriving in Hong Kong, we will go on a Hong Kong city tour to visit Garden Of Star & Starry Gallery, Victoria Peak (mid level exclude tram) where you can see views of Hong Kong city and the Kowloon peninsula, and visit Jiansazui Mosque. Shopping stop at Chocolate Shop and Jc Jewerly Workshop . Then we will head to Zhuhai via New Bridge the longest sea bridge in the world. Arriving you will have dinner, then check-in hotel (L,D)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Day 02: ZHUHAI – SHENZHEN</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\nBreakfast at the hotel. City tour Zhuhai visit The Lovers Road, Fishing Girl Statue. The journey continues to Shenzhen to visit Netherland Flower Town, Meilin Mosque, Herbal Shop, Jade Shop, Shenzhen Light Show, and shopping at Dongmen Street (B,L,D)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Day 03: SHENZHEN– HONGKONG</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\nToday after breakfast at the hotel, you can shop or take pictures around the hotel. Until the time you will be escorted to Hong Kong. Upon arrival you will visit the Kowloon Mosque and Jamiah Mosque. Then you will shop at the Hong Kong shopping center (B,LD)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <strong>Day 04 : HONGKONG – JAKARTA</strong>\r\n        <p>\r\nToday you will be transferred to the airport for your flight back to Jakarta. Thank you for your participation and see you at another travel destinations. (B)\r\n        </p>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>', 'HONGKONG SHENZHEN MUSLIM TOUR', 'HONGKONG SHENZHEN MUSLIM TOUR - English');

